      <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
      <article class="legal-content" aria-label="Privacy policy content">

        <div class="legal-intro">
          <p>
            Your privacy matters to us. This policy explains what information Value.Codes collects when you visit our website, why we collect it, and how we handle it. We've written this in plain language — not legalese — because we believe you deserve to understand what happens to your data.
          </p>
          <p>
            The short version: <strong>we collect very little, we don't sell your data, and most of our tools process everything locally in your browser.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>

        <section id="overview" class="legal-section">
          <h2>1. Overview</h2>
          <p>
            Value.Codes ("we", "our", "the Site") is a developer tools platform. By using value.codes, you agree to the collection and use of information as described in this policy.
          </p>
          <p>
            This policy applies to all pages and services on value.codes, including our tools, compiler, blog, and community features.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="information-collected" class="legal-section">
          <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
          <h3>2.1 Information You Provide Directly</h3>
          <p>When you interact with certain features, you may provide:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Account registration:</strong> Username, email address, and password (hashed and salted — never stored in plaintext).</li>
            <li><strong>Contact form:</strong> Your name, email address, and message when you reach out through our contact page.</li>
            <li><strong>Newsletter subscription:</strong> Email address if you choose to subscribe.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
          <p>When you visit Value.Codes, our servers and third-party services may automatically log:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Your IP address (for server security and rate limiting)</li>
            <li>Browser type and version</li>
            <li>Operating system</li>
            <li>Referring URL</li>
            <li>Pages visited and time spent on each page</li>
            <li>Approximate geographic location (country/city level, derived from IP)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.3 What We Do NOT Collect From Tools</h3>
          <p>
            All processing in our developer tools (JSON Formatter, Regex Builder, JWT Decoder, Hash Generator, Base64 Encoder, etc.) happens entirely in your browser. <strong>The data you paste or type into our tools is never transmitted to our servers.</strong> If you decode a JWT or hash a password — that computation happens locally. We never see it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="how-we-use-data" class="legal-section">
          <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
          <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Operate and improve the platform — fixing bugs, improving performance, shipping new features</li>
            <li>Respond to your messages and support requests</li>
            <li>Protect against fraud, abuse, and security threats (rate limiting, spam detection)</li>
            <li>Analyze aggregate usage patterns to understand which tools are most useful (anonymized traffic data only)</li>
            <li>Send newsletter updates if you've subscribed (you can unsubscribe any time)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal data to any third party. We do <strong>not</strong> use your data for behavioral advertising beyond what Google AdSense does through its standard ad serving (see Section 5).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="cookies" class="legal-section">
          <h2>4. Cookies &amp; Tracking</h2>
          <p>Value.Codes uses a minimal set of cookies:</p>
          <div class="legal-table-wrap">
            <table class="legal-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Cookie</th>
                  <th>Purpose</th>
                  <th>Duration</th>
                  <th>Type</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>session</code></td>
                  <td>Keeps you logged in to your account</td>
                  <td>7 days</td>
                  <td>Functional</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>cookie_consent</code></td>
                  <td>Remembers your cookie preference</td>
                  <td>1 year</td>
                  <td>Functional</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Google AdSense</td>
                  <td>Personalized or non-personalized ads</td>
                  <td>Up to 2 years</td>
                  <td>Advertising</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <p>
            You can control cookies through your browser settings at any time. Disabling functional cookies will prevent features like staying logged in from working properly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="google-adsense" class="legal-section">
          <h2>5. Google AdSense</h2>
          <p>
            Value.Codes uses Google AdSense to display advertisements. Google AdSense uses cookies and web beacons to serve ads based on your prior visits to this and other websites.
          </p>
          <p>
            Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visit to Value.Codes and/or other sites on the internet. If you'd prefer that Google not use your browsing history for interest-based ads, you can opt out at:
            <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">google.com/settings/ads</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            Alternatively, you can opt out of a third-party vendor's use of cookies for interest-based advertising by visiting:
            <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aboutads.info/choices</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            You can also learn more about how Google uses data when you use sites that partner with Google at:
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites</a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="third-party" class="legal-section">
          <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>Value.Codes integrates with the following third-party services:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Google AdSense</strong> — advertising. Governed by <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>ui-avatars.com</strong> — generates default avatar images based on your username initial. This request is made by your browser when viewing your profile. No personal data is shared beyond a single letter.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Pyodide (WebAssembly)</strong> — used in the online compiler to execute Python code entirely within your browser. No code is sent to external servers for Python execution.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not use Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, Hotjar, or other user-tracking services beyond AdSense.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="data-security" class="legal-section">
          <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
          <p>We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Passwords are hashed using bcrypt before storage — we cannot recover your plaintext password</li>
            <li>All connections to Value.Codes are encrypted via HTTPS</li>
            <li>Session cookies use the <code>httpOnly</code> and <code>secure</code> flags</li>
            <li>Our servers are protected by rate limiting and Helmet security headers</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            No system is 100% secure. In the unlikely event of a data breach that affects your personal information, we will notify you within 72 hours as required by applicable law.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="your-rights" class="legal-section">
          <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>Depending on where you live, you may have rights over your personal data, including:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Right to access</strong> — request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
            <li><strong>Right to correction</strong> — request that we correct inaccurate data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to deletion</strong> — request that we delete your account and associated data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> — receive your data in a structured format</li>
            <li><strong>Right to object</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            To exercise any of these rights, <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>. We will respond within 30 days.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="children" class="legal-section">
          <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Value.Codes is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> and we will delete it promptly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="changes" class="legal-section">
          <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this privacy policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. For significant changes, we may also add a notice on the homepage.
          </p>
          <p>
            Continued use of Value.Codes after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy. We encourage you to check this page periodically.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="contact-privacy" class="legal-section">
          <h2>11. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about this privacy policy, or want to exercise your rights, please reach out:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@value.codes">hello@value.codes</a></li>
            <li><strong>Contact form:</strong> <a href="/contact/">value.codes/contact</a></li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <div class="legal-footer-nav">
          <a href="/legal/terms-of-service" class="btn btn-secondary">Read Terms of Service &rarr;</a>
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-ghost">Have a question? Contact us &rarr;</a>
        </div>

      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
